{
  "$schema": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/oasis-tcs/sarif-spec/main/sarif-2.1/schema/sarif-schema-2.1.0.json",
  "version": "2.1.0",
  "runs": [
    {
      "tool": {
        "driver": {
          "name": "Tachi",
          "semanticVersion": "1.1",
          "informationUri": "https://github.com/tachi-tm/tachi",
          "supportedTaxonomies": [
            { "name": "OWASP", "index": 0 },
            { "name": "CWE", "index": 1 }
          ],
          "rules": [
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/spoofing",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Identity spoofing threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where an attacker assumes the identity of another entity — user, service, or system component — undermining authentication guarantees and enabling unauthorized actions under a trusted identity." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review authentication mechanisms, service-to-service identity verification, session management, and credential handling. Look for missing MFA, absent mTLS, unvalidated tokens, and predictable session identifiers.",
                "markdown": "**Detection guidance**: Review authentication mechanisms, service-to-service identity verification, session management, and credential handling.\n\n**Framework references**:\n- [OWASP A07:2021 — Identification and Authentication Failures](https://owasp.org/Top10/A07_2021-Identification_and_Authentication_Failures/)\n- [CWE-287: Improper Authentication](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/287.html)\n- MITRE ATT&CK T1078: Valid Accounts"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "spoofing", "authentication", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "A07", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-287", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/tampering",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Data tampering threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where an attacker modifies data, code, or configuration without authorization, violating integrity guarantees and causing systems to operate on corrupted inputs or persist falsified records." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review input validation, data flow integrity protection, storage access controls, and configuration management. Look for missing HMAC signatures, unsigned messages, direct database access without authorization, and mutable configuration stores.",
                "markdown": "**Detection guidance**: Review input validation, data flow integrity, storage access controls, and configuration management.\n\n**Framework references**:\n- [OWASP A08:2021 — Software and Data Integrity Failures](https://owasp.org/Top10/A08_2021-Software_and_Data_Integrity_Failures/)\n- [CWE-345: Insufficient Verification of Data Authenticity](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/345.html)\n- MITRE ATT&CK T1565: Data Manipulation"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "tampering", "integrity", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "8.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "A08", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-345", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/repudiation",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Repudiation threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where a user or system can deny having performed an action and the system lacks sufficient evidence to prove otherwise, undermining accountability and forensic capabilities." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review audit logging completeness, log integrity protection, timestamp management, and non-repudiation controls. Look for missing audit trails, mutable log storage, insufficient log detail, and unattributed actions.",
                "markdown": "**Detection guidance**: Review audit logging, log integrity, timestamp management, and non-repudiation controls.\n\n**Framework references**:\n- [OWASP A09:2021 — Security Logging and Monitoring Failures](https://owasp.org/Top10/A09_2021-Security_Logging_and_Monitoring_Failures/)\n- [CWE-778: Insufficient Logging](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/778.html)\n- MITRE ATT&CK T1070: Indicator Removal"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "repudiation", "logging", "accountability", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "8.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "A09", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-778", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/information-disclosure",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Information disclosure threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where sensitive information is exposed to unauthorized parties through direct data leaks, verbose error messages, side-channel observations, or insufficient access controls on stored data." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review error handling, API response filtering, data-at-rest encryption, data-in-transit protection, and access controls on stored data. Look for verbose error messages, unfiltered API responses, unencrypted sensitive data, and exposed debug endpoints.",
                "markdown": "**Detection guidance**: Review error handling, response filtering, encryption, and access controls.\n\n**Framework references**:\n- [OWASP A01:2021 — Broken Access Control](https://owasp.org/Top10/A01_2021-Broken_Access_Control/)\n- [CWE-200: Exposure of Sensitive Information](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/200.html)\n- MITRE ATT&CK T1005: Data from Local System"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "information-disclosure", "data-exposure", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "8.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "A01", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-200", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/denial-of-service",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Denial of service threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where an attacker degrades or eliminates system availability through resource exhaustion, flooding, algorithmic complexity exploitation, or cascading dependency failures." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review rate limiting, request size limits, connection pool management, timeout configuration, and circuit breaker patterns. Look for unbounded input sizes, missing rate limits, absent timeouts, and cascading failure paths.",
                "markdown": "**Detection guidance**: Review rate limiting, request size limits, timeouts, and circuit breakers.\n\n**Framework references**:\n- [OWASP A05:2021 — Security Misconfiguration](https://owasp.org/Top10/A05_2021-Security_Misconfiguration/)\n- [CWE-400: Uncontrolled Resource Consumption](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/400.html)\n- MITRE ATT&CK T1499: Endpoint Denial of Service"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "denial-of-service", "availability", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "A05", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-400", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/elevation-of-privilege",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Privilege escalation threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where an attacker gains higher privileges than authorized, performing actions reserved for administrators, accessing other users' resources, or bypassing access control boundaries." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review authorization enforcement, RBAC implementation, IDOR protections, network segmentation, and lateral movement controls. Look for missing authorization checks, user-controllable role assignments, and overly broad network policies.",
                "markdown": "**Detection guidance**: Review authorization, RBAC, IDOR protections, and network segmentation.\n\n**Framework references**:\n- [OWASP A01:2021 — Broken Access Control](https://owasp.org/Top10/A01_2021-Broken_Access_Control/)\n- [CWE-269: Improper Privilege Management](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/269.html)\n- MITRE ATT&CK T1548: Abuse Elevation Control Mechanism"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "elevation-of-privilege", "authorization", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "A01", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-269", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/ai/agentic-threats",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "AI agent autonomy and misuse threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats from autonomous agent systems operating with insufficient constraints on decision-making, action scope, or operational boundaries, and from agentic systems invoking external tools with inadequate access controls or parameter validation." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review agent iteration limits, human-in-the-loop checkpoints, tool access scoping, tool parameter validation, and resource budgets. Look for unbounded loops, missing approval gates, unscoped tool access, and absent chain depth limits.",
                "markdown": "**Detection guidance**: Review agent constraints, tool access controls, and resource limits.\n\n**Framework references**:\n- [OWASP Agentic Security Initiative (ASI)](https://owasp.org/www-project-agentic-security-initiative/)\n- [CWE-693: Protection Mechanism Failure](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/693.html)\n- MITRE ATLAS: Abuse of AI Agent Capabilities"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "ai", "agentic", "autonomy", "tool-use", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-693", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/ai/llm-threats",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "LLM-specific threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats specific to Large Language Model integrations including prompt injection, data poisoning of training and retrieval pipelines, model theft through systematic querying, and system prompt leakage." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review prompt boundary enforcement, input/output filtering, RAG pipeline content sanitization, model API access controls, and query monitoring. Look for raw prompt concatenation, unsanitized retrieved content, missing query limits, and exposed model metadata.",
                "markdown": "**Detection guidance**: Review prompt handling, content sanitization, API access controls, and query monitoring.\n\n**Framework references**:\n- [OWASP LLM Top 10 v2025](https://genai.owasp.org/)\n- [CWE-74: Improper Neutralization of Special Elements in Output](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/74.html)\n- MITRE ATLAS: LLM Prompt Injection (AML.T0051)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "ai", "llm", "prompt-injection", "data-poisoning", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-74", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      },
